  <article class='journals'>
		<h2 id="columns">Problem Columns from Mathematics Journals</h2>
<p>Many mathematics journals contain problem columns. They invite readers
to send in solutions to the problems. The best solution submitted
gets printed in a future issue along with the names of all the solvers.

We list below only a few of the journals that are currently running
problem columns. You are welcome to try your hand at
solving these problems. Solutions should be sent to the appropriate problem
column editor (<b>not</b> to MathPro Press).</p>
    
<ul>
  <li id='fq'>The Fibonacci Quarterly</li>
	<ul>
    <li><a href="problemColumns/fq/fqInstructions.html">Instructions for Contributoros</a></li>
    <li><a href="problemColumns/fq/fqInfo.html">About the Journal</a></li>
    <li><a href="problemColumns/fq/fqArchive.html">Problem Column Archive</a></li>
      
    <li>Current Problems</li>
    <ul>
      <li>Volume 32 Issue #4 - August 1994 (deadline: May 1, 1995)</li>
      <p class='fibonacci'>Problems 766-771</p>
      <ol>
        
        <li><a href="problemColumns/fq/Aug1994.html">web page</a></li>
        <li><a href="problemColumns/fq/Aug1994.dvi">dvi</a></li>
      </ol>
      
      <li>Volume 32 Issue #5 - November 1994 (deadline: August 1, 1995)</li>
      <p class='fibonacci'>Problems 772-777</p>
      <ol>
        
        <li><a href="problemColumns/fq/Nov1994.html">web page</a></li>
        <li><a href="problemColumns/fq/Nov1994.dvi">dvi</a></li>
      </ol>
      
      <li>Volume 33 Issue #1 - February 1995 (deadline: November 1, 1995)</li>
      <p class='fibonacci'>Problems 778-783</p>
      <ol>
        <li><a href="problemColumns/fq/Feb1995.html">web page</a></li>
        <li><a href="problemColumns/fq/Feb1995.dvi">dvi</a></li>
     </ol>
      
      <li>Volume 33 Issue #2 - May 1995 (deadline: February 1, 1996)</li>
       <p class='fibonacci'>Problems 784-789</p>
      <ol>
        <li><a href="problemColumns/fq/May1995.html">web page</a></li>
